        "content": "{\"units\":[{\"declaration_names\":[\"AlgebraicCombinatorics.fps_invertible_iff_constantCoeff_field\"],\"lean_file_body\":\"namespace AlgebraicCombinatorics\\n\\ntheorem fps_invertible_iff_constantCoeff_field {K : Type*} [Field K] (a : PowerSeries K) :\\n    IsUnit a ↔ constantCoeff a ≠ 0 := by\\n  rw [fps_invertible_iff_constantCoeff]\\n  constructor\\n  · intro h\\n    rcases h with ⟨u, hu⟩\\n    rw [← hu]\\n    exact Units.ne_zero u\\n  · intro h\\n    exact ⟨Units.mk0 (constantCoeff a) h, rfl⟩\\n\\nend AlgebraicCombinatorics\",\"notes\":[\"Uses the prior project theorem reducing invertibility of a power series to invertibility of its constant coefficient. Over a field, an invertible scalar is nonzero by destructing the IsUnit witness, and a nonzero scalar gives a unit via Units.mk0.\"],\"status\":\"generated\",\"unit_key\":\"unit-002\",\"used_context\":[\"AlgebraicCombinatorics.fps_invertible_iff_constantCoeff\",\"Units.ne_zero\",\"Units.mk0\",\"Field K\"]}]}",
